rows.label: qst103910_msg0001
rows.name:
You really saved my bacon...
Thanks, strangers.

rows.label: qst103910_msg0002
rows.name:
I'm transporting goods between
Rigitte and Ysheva Harbor.

rows.label: qst103910_msg0003
rows.name:
But there's some food or something
in here, and once those blackguards
get a whiff they don't let up.

rows.label: qst103910_msg0004
rows.name:
So you want to know how much it
costs to get money to Iyasaki?

rows.label: qst103910_msg0005
rows.name:
Well, first the Superbian ship
docks in the harbor.

rows.label: qst103910_msg0006
rows.name:
Then the goods are sent through
Orl Cloudway to Ysheva Harbor.

rows.label: qst103910_msg0007
rows.name:
There are a lot of monsters in the
Cloud Sea, so I have to hire guards.

rows.label: qst103910_msg0008
rows.name:
So lessee... I take 2,500G...and the
guards are 1,700G each, there's
three of them, so...

rows.label: qst103910_msg0009
rows.name:
If I get 66,554G, your Correl will
wind up receiving 58,954G.

rows.label: qst103910_msg0010
rows.name:
You started with 90,000G?
Whew. Tough break, kiddo.

rows.label: qst103910_msg0011
rows.name:
If there were a direct shipping route to
Ysheva Harbor, there'd be fewer middle
men and it'd be cheaper, eh?

rows.label: qst103910_msg0012
rows.name:
You'll help? That would be
excellent! Avaritia produces
some really nice stuff.

rows.label: qst103910_msg0013
rows.name:
But it's not like I have access to
long-haul Divine Beast ships way out here.

rows.label: qst103910_msg0014
rows.name:
Looks like I'll have to go begging
to the Avaritia Trade Guild.

rows.label: qst103910_msg0015
rows.name:
If we can really do this,
the people of Iyasaki
are going to be very happy.

rows.label: qst103910_msg0101
rows.name:
My current client is a
bit of a stingy one.

rows.label: qst103910_msg0102
rows.name:
So I couldn't afford to pay any
bodyguards. I thought I'd be OK
on my own, but it turns out I wasn't.
